snippet.textDisplay:
Neighbouring regions

Outside Odisha, there are also significant Odia-speaking populations in other linguistic regions, such as the Midnapore district ofWest Bengal, the East Singhbhum, West Singhbhum Seraikela Kharsawan district,Simdega, Gumla, Khunti, Ranchi district ofJharkhand, the Srikakulam, Vizianagaram andVishakhapatnam District of Andhra Pradesh, eastern districts of Chhattisgarh state. Due to the increasing migration of labour, the west Indian state of Gujarat[12] also has a significant Odia-speaking population withSurat being the city with the second largest[citation needed] Odia-speaking population in India. The Odia-speaking people are also found in significant numbers in the cities ofVishakhapatnam, Hyderabad, Pondicherry,Bangalore, Chennai, Goa, Mumbai, Raipur,Jamshedpur, Baroda, Ahmedabad, New Delhi,Kolkata, Kharagpur, Guwahati, Shillong, Pune, and Silvassa in India.[13]

Foreign countries

The Odia diaspora constitute a sizeable number in several countries around the world. They are significant in number in countries such as Bangladesh, Indonesia, mainly carried by sadhaba, the ancient traders from Odisha who carried the language along with the culture during the old-day trading,[14] and in western countries such as the United States,Canada, Australia and England. Odia speakers are regarded as one of the ‘Transnational Ethnic Indian Groups’. In India, the language is spoken by over 31 million people, and globally over 45 million speak Odia. It is one of the official languages of India and the major language of Odisha. Odia language has spread also to Burma, Malaysia, Fiji, Sri Lankaand Pakistan.[15]

Bottom line is don't underestimate the power of Odia language...

ଧନ୍ୟବାଦ Sona ମୋହପତ୍ରା ,ଋତୁ ରାଜ, ରାମ ସମ୍ପାଥ୍ ଓ MTV Coke ସତୁଡିଓ. ପୁରୁଣା ଓଡିୟା ଗୀତ କୁ ଏଭଳି international stage ରେ ପେରଫୋର୍ମ୍ କରିବା ପୈଂ. ଇଣ୍ଡିଆନ୍ cinema Bollywood ରେ ଓଡିୟା କଲାକାର୍ ମନଂକ ର ନମୋ ନିସନ୍ ନାହି. ଏଭଳି ଗୋଟେ ଭଲ ପଦଖପ ନିସ୍ଚିତ ସ୍ବାଗତ ଯୋଗ୍ୟ.
ରଂଗବତୀ ଗୀତ ଅଗରୁ ବହୁତ୍ ଥର cinema ରେ ଉସେ ହେଇଚି, ସେତେ ବେଳେ copy right act କୁଆଡେ ଜେଇଥିଲା.
wikipedia ଅନୁସାରେ  'The song is featured in Bollywood movie Kaun Kitne Pani Mein.' ଅଣ୍ଡ "Rangabati" was recreated in many other languages of India and has been recreated in Telugu for a movie.
ସମୟ ର ତଳେ ତଳେ ଚାଲିବା ଦରକାର୍...ସେ ସମୟ ରେ ଓରିଗିନାଲ୍ ହିତ ଥିଲା କିନ୍ତୁ ଏବେକାର generation ପଇଁ ଗୀତ updtae ନିହାତି ଦରକାର୍. ***** Sona Mohapatra Rituraj Mohanty

snippet.textDisplay: I am really ashamed of such type of act to defame such an incredible song. They  really have spoiled the song. Though it was a good try and still the song was good, the introduction of the wrappers was actually bullshit.They started well, but the repeated pronunciation of Rangabati as Ranga,Ranga,Ranga.....was rough to listen. At the end they tried to give some punch of Bande Utkala Janani,which could revive the beauty of the song to some extent. Initially I liked the song when it was at the beginning. But after the completion of the song I felt that they destroyed their own attempt. I also support remix of old to new and to represent the glorious songs of odisha to all over the world. Though this attempt had begun at the right track in the beginning, but finally was derailed. Hence for me such type of act should be abandoned.
